==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pachydermata
<hw>Pach`y*der"ma*ta</hw>
<pr>(p⟦acr⟧k`⟦icr⟧*d⟦etil⟧r"m⟦adot⟧*t⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>pachy`dermos</grk> thick-skinned;
<grk>pachy`s</grk> thick + <grk>de`rma</grk> skin.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A group of hoofed mammals distinguished for the
thickness of their skins, including the elephant, hippopotamus,
rhinoceros, tapir, horse, and hog; the pachyderms. It is now considered
an artificial group.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>pachydermatosis</ent>⟦br⟧
